t-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Number</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-900\">3</p></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Day</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900\">Friday</p></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Colors</p><div class=\"mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2\"><span class=\"rounded-full bg-white px-3 py-1 text-sm text-slate-700 ring-1 ring-slate-200\">Red</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-white px-3 py-1 text-sm text-slate-700 ring-1 ring-slate-200\">Yellow</span></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Stone</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900\">Emerald</p></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Life Path Number</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900\">4</p></div></div><div class=\"mt-4 rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\"><span class=\"font-semibold text-slate-900\">Numerology meaning:</span> <!-- -->Patience, hard work, stability</div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-heart h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M2 9.5a5.5 5.5 0 0 1 9.591-3.676.56.56 0 0 0 .818 0A5.49 5.49 0 0 1 22 9.5c0 2.29-1.5 4-3 5.5l-5.492 5.313a2 2 0 0 1-3 .019L5 15c-1.5-1.5-3-3.2-3-5.5\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Personality</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Personality Traits</h2></div></div><div class=\"flex flex-wrap gap-2\"><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Kind</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Faithful</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Courageous</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Wise</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">L = Loyal</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">F = Faithful</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">S = Strong</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">C = Compassionate</span></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-book-text h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2H19a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v18a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H6.5a1 1 0 0 1 0-5H20\"></path><path d=\"M8 11h8\"></path><path d=\"M8 7h6\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Spiritual</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Spiritual Significance</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-slate-800 leading-7\">Symbolizes overcoming adversity and deception.</div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-shield h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Cultural Context</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Cultural Significance</h2></div></div><div class=\"space-y-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\"><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\">James, as a common name in the English-speaking world, has significant historical and cultural connections. The name has been borne by many eminent figures across various fields, including James Clerk Maxwell, the renowned Scottish physicist, and James Madison, the fourth President of the United States. The name also appears often in works of literature and popular culture, such as in Shakespeare&#x27;s play &quot;Julius Caesar,&quot; where Brutus laments, &quot;Ewise the noble James his life represses; / Himself hath quell&#x27;d him, with no sword to parry.&quot;</div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\">For Christians, the name James evokes reverence and respect due to its association with several prominent figures in the New Testament. One of these is James, son of Zebedee, who is mentioned twice among the twelve apostles. James was a son of Zebedee and Salome, and a brother of John the Beloved. Some scholars believe that James was executed by Herod Agrippa I in Jerusalem around AD 42. James&#x27;s symbol is often represented by the pilgrim&#x27;s staff, indicating the role of a shepherd in guiding others toward the path of righteousness. In addition, the Book of James in the New Testament offers guidance on practical Christian living, emphasizing faith and works as essential components of a faithful life.</div><p class=\"rounded-3xl bg-blue-50 p-4 text-sm text-blue-800\">Biblical reference: <!-- -->Genesis 25:26<!-- --> — The name James/יעקב is mentioned throughout the Bible, notably in the book of Genesis as the son of Isaac and Rebekah</p><p class=\"rounded-3xl bg-purple-50 p-4 text-sm text-purple-800\">Saint connection: <!-- -->Saint James<!-- --> — The name James is associated with Saint James the Greater and Saint James the Lesser, both apostles of Jesus Christ</p></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-clock h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"></circle><path d=\"M12 6v6l4 2\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Historical Usage</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Historical References</h2></div></div><div class=\"space-y-4\"><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">Historical records show that James, son of Zebedee, one of the twelve apostles of Jesus. The name James carried significant spiritual weight in that era.</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Late 1st century AD</p></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">James, brother of Jesus, also known as James the Just, was the bishop of Jerusalem and leader of the early Christian Church.</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Early 1st century AD</p></div></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-sparkles h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M11.017 2.814a1 1 0 0 1 1.966 0l1.051 5.558a2 2 0 0 0 1.594 1.594l5.558 1.051a1 1 0 0 1 0 1.966l-5.558 1.051a2 2 0 0 0-1.594 1.594l-1.051 5.558a1 1 0 0 1-1.966 0l-1.051-5.558a2 2 0 0 0-1.594-1.594l-5.558-1.051a1 1 0 0 1 0-1.966l5.558-1.051a2 2 0 0 0 1.594-1.594z\"></path><path d=\"M20 2v4\"></path><path d=\"M22 4h-4\"></path><circle cx=\"4\" cy=\"20\" r=\"2\"></circle></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Spiritual</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Spiritual Symbolism</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-slate-800 leading-7\">James: The name James is derived from the Hebrew name Jacob, which means &quot;supplanter&quot; or &quot;deceiver&quot; due to his deceitful acquisition of the birthright. In Christianity, James represents faith that leads to works and humility, embodying the virtues of obedience and service to others.</div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-trending-up h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M16 7h6v6\"></path><path d=\"m22 7-8.5 8.5-5-5L2 17\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Modern Usage</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Modern Usage</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\">&lt;p&gt;The name James has gained popularity in various modern contexts. Some well-known individuals with this name have made significant strides in technology entrepreneurship, sports commentary, and politics and public speaking. Tech entrepreneurs like James Pallotta, founder and CEO of Vistaprint, and James Wimbley, co-founder of Coinbase, have shown the versatility of this name in the business world. In the sports commentary realm, James Brown, the lead NFL insider for the NFL Network, and James Cybulski, a popular sports broadcaster, have made their mark with their insightful analysis and engaging personalities. Lastly, in politics and public speaking, James Carville, a political consultant, and James Corden, a television host, have gained widespread recognition for their respective contributions to their fields.&lt;/p&gt;</div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-trending-up h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M16 7h6v6\"></path><path d=\"m22 7-8.5 8.5-5-5L2 17\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Popularity</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Popularity by Region</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\"><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Brazil</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->100</span></div><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Poland</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->98</span></div><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">United Kingdom</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->100</span></div><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Italy</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->100</span></div></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-award h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m15.477 12.89 1.515 8.526a.5.5 0 0 1-.81.47l-3.58-2.687a1 1 0 0 0-1.197 0l-3.586 2.686a.5.5 0 0 1-.81-.469l1.514-8.526\"></path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"8\" r=\"6\"></circle></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Famous People</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Famous People and Real-World Usage</h2></div></div><p class=\"text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500 mb-3\">Historical Figures &amp