text-slate-700 leading-7\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\",\"children\":\"James, as a common name in the English-speaking world, has significant historical and cultural connections. The name has been borne by many eminent figures across various fields, including James Clerk Maxwell, the renowned Scottish physicist, and James Madison, the fourth President of the United States. The name also appears often in works of literature and popular culture, such as in Shakespeare's play \\\"Julius Caesar,\\\" where Brutus laments, \\\"Ewise the noble James his life represses; / Himself hath quell'd him, with no sword to parry.\\\"\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\",\"children\":\"For Christians, the name James evokes reverence and respect due to its association with several prominent figures in the New Testament. One of these is James, son of Zebedee, who is mentioned twice among the twelve apostles. James was a son of Zebedee and Salome, and a brother of John the Beloved. Some scholars believe that James was executed by Herod Agrippa I in Jerusalem around AD 42. James's symbol is often represented by the pilgrim's staff, indicating the role of a shepherd in guiding others toward the path of righteousness. In addition, the Book of James in the New Testament offers guidance on practical Christian living, emphasizing faith and works as essential components of a faithful life.\"}],\"$undefined\",\"$undefined\",[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-blue-50 p-4 text-sm text-blue-800\",\"children\":[\"Biblical reference: \",\"Genesis 25:26\",\" — The name James/יעקב is mentioned throughout the Bible, notably in the book of Genesis as the son of Isaac and Rebekah\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-purple-50 p-4 text-sm text-purple-800\",\"children\":[\"Saint connection: \",\"Saint James\",\" — The name James is associated with Saint James the Greater and Saint James the Lesser, both apostles of Jesus Christ\"]}]]}]]}]\n61:[\"$\",\"$L71\",null,{\"className\":\"my-6\",\"minHeight\":\"90px\",\"instanceId\":\"name-detail-mid\"}]\n62:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-card\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L1a\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":\"$58:props:children:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-clock h-5 w-5\"}]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\",\"children\":\"Historical Usage\"}],[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Historical References\"}],\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\",\"children\":\"Historical records show that James, son of Zebedee, one of the twelve apostles of Jesus. The name James carried significant spiritual weight in that era.\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\",\"children\":\"Late 1st century AD\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\",\"children\":\"James, brother of Jesus, also known as James the Just, was the bishop of Jerusalem and leader of the early Christian Church.\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\",\"children\":\"Early 1st century AD\"}]]}]]}]]}]\n63:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-card\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L1a\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":\"$5d:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:children:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-sparkles h-5 w-5\"}]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\",\"children\":\"Spiritual\"}],[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Spiritual Symbolism\"}],\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-slate-800 leading-7\",\"children\":\"James: The name James is derived from the Hebrew name Jacob, which means \\\"supplanter\\\" or \\\"deceiver\\\" due to his deceitful acquisition of the birthright. In Christianity, James represents faith that leads to works and humility, embodying the virtues of obedience and service to others.\"}]]}]\n64:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-card\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L1a\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":[[\"path\",{\"d\":\"M16 7h6v6\",\"key\":\"box55l\"}],[\"path\",{\"d\":\"m22 7-8.5 8.5-5-5L2 17\",\"key\":\"1t1m79\"}]],\"className\":\"lucide-trending-up h-5 w-5\"}]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\",\"children\":\"Modern Usage\"}],[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Modern Usage\"}],\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\",\"children\":\"<p>The name James has gained popularity in various modern contexts. Some well-known individuals with this name have made significant strides in technology entrepreneurship, sports commentary, and politics and public speaking. Tech entrepreneurs like James Pallotta, founder and CEO of Vistaprint, and James Wimbley, co-founder of Coinbase, have shown the versatility of this name in the business world. In the sports commentary realm, James Brown, the lead NFL insider for the NFL Network, and James Cybulski, a popular sports broadcaster, have made their mark with their insightful analysis and engaging personalities. Lastly, in politics and public speaking, James Carville, a political consultant, and James Corden, a television host, have gained widespread recognition for their respective contributions to their fields.</p>\"}]]}]\n65:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-card\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L1a\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":\"$64:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:children:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-trending-up h-5 w-5\"}]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\",\"children\":\"Popularity\"}],[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Popularity by Region\"}],\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\",\"children\":[[\"