hildren\":\"/ˈdʒeɪmz/\"}]]}],false]}]]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-card\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\",\"children\":\"$L59\"}],\"$L5a\"]}],\"$L5b\"]}],\"$L5c\",\"$L5d\",\"$L5e\",\"$L5f\",\"$L60\",\"$L61\",\"$L62\",\"$L63\",\"$L64\",\"$L65\",\"$L66\",false,\"$L67\"]}],\"$L68\"]}]\n56:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-stack\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L69\",null,{\"data\":{\"_id\":\"694a591ba576fe65e062f42e\",\"name\":\"James\",\"slug\":\"james\",\"language\":[\"English\",\"Hebrew\",\"Greek\",\"Latin\"],\"gender\":\"(Male)\",\"origin\":\"Biblical\",\"religion\":\"christian\",\"category\":\"Saint\",\"short_meaning\":\"Supplanter\",\"long_meaning\":\"From the Hebrew name 'Yaqob' which means 'deceiver' or 'supplanter', or from the Greek name 'Iakobos' which means 'the name of a man who follows a supplanter, or 'the supplanter'.' In the New Testament, James is the name of several individuals, including James the son of Zebedee, one of the twelve apostles.\",\"spiritual_meaning\":\"Symbolizes overcoming adversity and deception.\",\"emotional_traits\":[\"Kind\",\"Faithful\",\"Courageous\",\"Wise\"],\"hidden_personality_traits\":[\"L = Loyal\",\"F = Faithful\",\"S = Strong\",\"C = Compassionate\"],\"lucky_number\":3,\"lucky_day\":\"Friday\",\"lucky_colors\":[\"Red\",\"Yellow\"],\"lucky_stone\":\"Emerald\",\"life_path_number\":4,\"numerology_meaning\":\"Patience, hard work, stability\",\"in_hebrew\":{\"name\":\"יעקב\",\"meaning\":\"הוא יחליף, יעקב הוא שמו של הבן של יצחק\"},\"in_greek\":{\"name\":\"Ιακώβος\",\"meaning\":\"αυτός ο οποίος πατάει τη φτέρνα\"},\"in_latin\":{\"name\":\"Iacobus\",\"meaning\":\"supplanter, heel grabber\"},\"in_english\":{\"name\":\"James\",\"meaning\":\"supplanter, one who replaces or follows\"},\"pronunciation\":{\"english\":\"JAYMZ\",\"ipa\":\"/ˈdʒeɪmz/\"},\"celebrity_usage\":[\"James Corden\",\"James Franco\",\"James Earl Jones\"],\"social_tags\":[\"#JamesMeaning\",\"#ChristianBabyNames\",\"#BibleNames\",\"#ChristianNames\",\"#James\"],\"name_variations\":[],\"popularity_score\":100,\"popularity_by_region\":[{\"region\":\"Brazil\",\"country_code\":\"BR\",\"score\":100,\"year\":2024,\"_id\":\"694a591ba576fe65e062f42f\"},{\"region\":\"Poland\",\"country_code\":\"PL\",\"score\":98,\"year\":2024,\"_id\":\"694a591ba576fe65e062f430\"},{\"region\":\"United Kingdom\",\"country_code\":\"UK\",\"score\":100,\"year\":2024,\"_id\":\"694a591ba576fe65e062f431\"},{\"region\":\"Italy\",\"country_code\":\"IT\",\"score\":100,\"year\":2024,\"_id\":\"694a591ba576fe65e062f432\"}],\"biblical_reference\":{\"is_biblical\":true,\"origin_scripture\":\"Genesis\",\"verse_reference\":\"Genesis 25:26\",\"note\":\"The name James/יעקב is mentioned throughout the Bible, notably in the book of Genesis as the son of Isaac and Rebekah\"},\"saint_reference\":{\"is_saint_name\":true,\"saint_name\":\"Saint James\",\"note\":\"The name James is associated with Saint James the Greater and Saint James the Lesser, both apostles of Jesus Christ\"},\"cultural_impact\":\"James, as a common name in the English-speaking world, has significant historical and cultural connections. The name has been borne by many eminent figures across various fields, including James Clerk Maxwell, the renowned Scottish physicist, and James Madison, the fourth President of the United States. The name also appears often in works of literature and popular culture, such as in Shakespeare's play \\\"Julius Caesar,\\\" where Brutus laments, \\\"Ewise the noble James his life represses; / Himself hath quell'd him, with no sword to parry.\\\"\",\"spiritual_significance\":\"For Christians, the name James evokes reverence and respect due to its association with several prominent figures in the New Testament. One of these is James, son of Zebedee, who is mentioned twice among the twelve apostles. James was a son of Zebedee and Salome, and a brother of John the Beloved. Some scholars believe that James was executed by Herod Agrippa I in Jerusalem around AD 42. James's symbol is often represented by the pilgrim's staff, indicating the role of a shepherd in guiding others toward the path of righteousness. In addition, the Book of James in the New Testament offers guidance on practical Christian living, emphasizing faith and works as essential components of a faithful life.\",\"historical_references\":[{\"reference\":\"Historical records show that James, son of Zebedee, one of the twelve apostles of Jesus. The name James carried significant spiritual weight in that era.\",\"time_period\":\"Late 1st century AD\",\"context\":\"New Testament, Bible\",\"_id\":\"68925c5a5a4bd83e9b69e5e3\"},{\"reference\":\"James, brother of Jesus, also known as James the Just, was the bishop of Jerusalem and leader of the early Christian Church.\",\"time_period\":\"Early 1st century AD\",\"context\":\"New Testament, Bible\",\"_id\":\"68925c5a5a4bd83e9b69e5e4\"}],\"modern_usage\":{\"trends\":[\"Tech entrepreneurship\",\"Sports commentary\",\"Politics and public speaking\"],\"platforms\":[\"LinkedIn\",\"Twitter\",\"YouTube\"],\"modern_context\":\"<p>The name James has gained popularity in various modern contexts. Some well-known individuals with this name have made significant strides in technology entrepreneurship, sports commentary, and politics and public speaking. Tech entrepreneurs like James Pallotta, founder and CEO of Vistaprint, and James Wimbley, co-founder of Coinbase, have shown the versatility of this name in the business world. In the sports commentary realm, James Brown, the lead NFL insider for the NFL Network, and James Cybulski, a popular sports broadcaster, have made their mark with their insightful analysis and engaging personalities. Lastly, in politics and public speaking, James Carville, a political consultant, and James Corden, a television host, have gained widespread recognition for their respective contributions to their fields.</p>\"},\"name_in_real_life\":{\"person_name\":\"Sarah James\",\"location\":\"London, United Kingdom\",\"story\":\"A devoted Christian named Sarah James in London, United Kingdom credits much of their spiritual journey to their name James, which means \\\"Supplanter\\\". They believe their name has been a blessing and reminder of God's presence in their life.\"},\"spiritual_symbolism\":\"James: The name James is derived from the Hebrew name Jacob, which means \\\"supplanter\\\" or \\\"deceiver\\\" due to his deceitful acquisition of the birthright. In Christianity, James represents faith that leads to works and humility, embodying the virtues of obedience and service to others.\",\"seo\":{\"seo\":{\"title\":\"James - Meaning, Origin, and Cultural Significance for Christians\",\"meta_description\":\"Explore the meaning and religious value of the name James, its origin, and how it's used in Christianity.\",\"description_paragraph\":\"The name James is rooted in the Hebrew and Greek languages and holds significant cultural and religious value for Christians. Derived from the Hebrew name 'Yaqob', which means 'deceiver' or 'supplanter', the name James can be traced back to the Old Testament. In the New Testament, James is the name of several individuals, including James the son of Zebedee, one of the twelve apostles. With its rich history and religious significance, the name James remains a popular choice for Christian parents today.\",\"keywords\":[\"James name meaning\",\"Christian name James\",\"James origin\",\"James biblical meaning\",\"James religious significance\"],\"faq\":[{\"q\":\"What does James mean?\",\"a\":\"The name James is derived from the Hebrew name 'Yaqob', which means 'deceiver' or 'supplanter'. In the New Testament, it's the name of several individuals, including James the son of Zebedee, one of the twelve apostles.\"},{\"q\":\"Is James a Christianity name?\",\"a\":\"Yes, James is a popular name in Christianity, derived from the Old Testament and mentioned in the New Testament as the name of several individuals.\"},{\"q\":\"How to pronounce James?\",\"a\":\"The name James is pronounced as 'JAY-mus' or 'JAY-mz'.\"},{\"q\":\"Is James popular today?\",\"a\":\"Yes, James is a popular name for boys in the United States and many other countries.\"},{\"q\":\"What is the origin of James?\",\"a\":\"The name James originates from the Hebrew name 'Yaqob', which means 'deceiver' or 'supplanter', and from the Greek name 'Iakobos', which means 'the name of a man who follows a supplanter, or 'the supplanter'.' In the New Testament, James is the name of several individuals, including James the son of Zebedee, one of the twelve apostles.\"}]},\"title\":\"James Name Meaning in (Hebrew, Greek) | Christianity\",\"meta_description\":\"Discover the meaning of James, a beautiful Christian name meaning \\\"Supplanter\\\". Learn about its Biblical origin, spiritual significance, and cultural importance in Christian tradition.\",\"description_paragraph\":\"James is a meaningful Christian name of (Hebrew, Greek) origin that means \\\"Supplanter\\\". From the Hebrew name 'Yaqob' which means 'deceiver' or 'supplanter', or from the Greek name 'Iakobos' which means 'the name of a man who follows a supplanter, or 'the supplanter'.' In the New Testament, James is the name of several individuals, including James the son of Zebedee, one of the twelve apostles. Parents choosing this name for their child seek to bestow blessings and godly attributes upon them.\",\"keywords\":[\"James\",\"Christianity name\",\"(Hebrew, Greek) origin\",\"James meaning\"],\"faq\":[{\"q\":\"What does James mean?\",\"a\":\"James means \\\"Supplanter\\\" and is a popular Christian name with deep spiritual significance.\"},{\"q\":\"Is James a good Christian name?\",\"a\":\"Yes, James is a beautiful Christian name that carries positive meaning and is widely used in Christian communities around the world.\"},{\"q\":\"What is the origin of the name James?\",\"a\":\"James has (Hebrew, Greek) origins and is rooted in Christian tradition and culture.\"},{\"q\":\"Is James mentioned in the Bible?\",\"a\":\"James is a name with Biblical connections and carries significance in Christian scripture and tradition.\"},{\"q\":\"What are the spiritual benefits of naming a child James?\",\"a\":\"Naming a child James is believed to bring blessings and embodies the beautiful meaning of \\\"Supplanter\\\", which can inspire godly character traits.\"}]},\"monetization\":{\"google_ads\":true,\"sponsored_content\":false},\"updated_at\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.423Z\",\"similar_sounding_names\":[\"abeliel\",\"Abijah\",\"Adalyn\",\"Adelaide\",\"Adele\",\"Adonella\",\"Agnes\",\"Agnieszka\",\"Aimee\",\"Alarice\"],\"related_names\":[]},\"religion\":\"christian\"}]}]\n57:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-stack\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-card-solid\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L1a\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":[[\"rect\",{\"width\":\"7\",\"height\":\"9\",\"x\":\"3\",\"y\":\"3\",\"rx\":\"1\",\"key\":\"10lvy0\"}],[\"rect\",{\"width\":\"7\",\"height\":\"5\",\"x\":\"14\",\"y\":\"3\",\"rx\":\"1\",\"key\":\"16une8\"}],[\"rect\",{\"width\":\"7\",\"height\":\"9\",\"x\":\"14\",\"y\":\"12\",\"rx\":\"1\",\"key\":\"1hutg5\"}],[\"rect\",{\"width\":\"7\",\"height\":\"5\",\"x\":\"3\",\"y\":\"16\",\"rx\":\"1\",\"key\":\"ldoo1y\"}]],\"className\":\"lucide-layout-dashboard h-5 w-5\"}]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900\",\"children\":[\"Explore Related \",\"Christian\",\" Name Collections\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\